President Biden has nominated Dr. Monica Bertagnolli as the Director of the National Institutes of Health (NIH). Dr. Bertagnolli is a renowned surgical oncologist, cancer researcher, educator, and physician-leader. She has been instrumental in advancing cancer prevention and treatment through her work as the Director of the National Cancer Institute. Dr. Bertagnolli has also led efforts to improve access to quality care and clinical trials for patients. She has a strong background in clinical and research oncology and has championed collaborative initiatives in cancer research. Dr. Bertagnolli's nomination reflects President Biden's commitment to promoting scientific discovery and improving healthcare for all Americans.